* description
  weather_catcher is a simple tool to get weather info in the web page
  through parsing the content.
* install and uninstall
  make example
  make example-conky
  make install
  make install prefix=/custom/path
  make uninstall
* binary
  /usr/bin/weather_catcher, a wrapper to run the main script weather_catcher.sh
  /usr/bin/weather_catcher_conky_example, just for showing the conky example
* usage
  weather_catcher.sh [-p parser] [-a argument] [-d datatype]
      [-n nightmode] [-f futureday] [-t tempunit] [-l] [-D] [-h] [-v]

  too see complete help message, type "weather_catcher.sh -h"
  too see parser's help message, type "weather_catcher.sh -p baidu -h"
* examples
  - print all weather info today
    weather_catcher.sh
    weather_catcher.sh -p baidu -a tianqi -d ALL
  - print tomorrow's weather text
    weather_catcher.sh -d WT -f 1
  - print weather font, use night mode
    weather_catcher.sh -d WF -n night
  - use a custom parser
    weather_catcher.sh -p your_parser.sh -a argument
  - print a parser's help message
    weather_catcher.sh -p baidu -h
